<h2>FAQs About Gluten-Free No-Bake Desserts</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>1. Can I use regular oats in gluten-free no-bake desserts?</h3>
    <p>No, regular oats are often cross-contaminated with gluten during processing. Always use certified gluten-free oats to ensure your desserts are safe for those with gluten sensitivities.</p>

    <h3>2. Are no-bake desserts healthier than baked ones?</h3>
    <p>Not necessarily. While no-bake desserts often use fewer processed ingredients, their healthiness depends on the specific recipe and ingredients used. However, they can be a healthier option if made with natural sweeteners and whole foods.</p>

    <h3>3. Can I substitute honey with another sweetener?</h3>
    <p>Yes, you can use other natural sweeteners like maple syrup, agave nectar, or even stevia. Just adjust the quantity to taste, as some sweeteners are sweeter than others.</p>

    <h3>4. How long do no-bake desserts last in the refrigerator?</h3>
    <p>Most no-bake desserts can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 5 days. However, it's best to check the specific recipe for storage recommendations.</p>

    <h3>5. Can I freeze no-bake desserts?</h3>
    <p>Yes, many no-bake desserts can be frozen for up to 3 months. Just make sure to store them in an airtight container to prevent freezer burn.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>Gluten-free no-bake desserts are a fantastic way to satisfy your sweet tooth without the hassle of baking or the worry of gluten. With just a few simple ingredients, you can create delicious and healthy treats that everyone will love. Whether you're in the mood for a rich chocolate mousse or a refreshing chia pudding, these desserts are sure to hit the spot. So, the next time you're craving something sweet, give one of these easy recipes a try!</p>

